# Docker Infrastructure

## Container Names

| Service | Container Name |
|---------|---------------|
| PostgreSQL Database | `sports-postgres` |
| Redis Cache | `sports-redis` |
| FastAPI Backend | `sports-backend` |
| Celery Worker | `sports-worker` |
| Next.js Frontend | `sports-frontend` |

## Common Commands

```powershell
# Start all services
docker compose up -d

# View logs
docker compose logs -f backend
docker compose logs -f worker

# Access PostgreSQL
docker exec -it sports-postgres psql -U sports -d sports_highlights

# Run SQL file (PowerShell)
Get-Content scripts/migrate.sql | docker exec -i sports-postgres psql -U sports -d sports_highlights

# Access Redis CLI
docker exec -it sports-redis redis-cli

# Restart a specific service
docker compose restart sports-backend
docker compose restart sports-worker
```

## Database Connection

- **Host**: `sports-postgres` (from within Docker) or `localhost` (from host)
- **Port**: `5432`
- **User**: `sports`
- **Database**: `sports_highlights`
